   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "title",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Echo-Check — LOF Encoder GPU Benchmark\n",
    "\n",
    "Tests the **LOF encoder** ONNX models (FP32 and INT8) on both CPU and GPU.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Models under test:**\n",
    "- `encoder_simplified.onnx` — FP32, graph-optimised\n",
    "- `encoder_int8.onnx` — INT8 static quantised (QDQ, 74.4% smaller)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Architecture:** Conv2D encoder → 128-dim embedding  \n",
    "**Input:** `(1, 1, 128, 432)` mel spectrogram  \n",
    "**Output:** `(1, 128)` latent embedding → scored by LOF\n",
    "\n",
    "> Runtime: Change to **GPU → T4** before running (`Runtime > Change runtime type`)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1 — Install dependencies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "install",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!pip install -q onnx onnxruntime-gpu"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2 — Upload ONNX files\n",
    "\n",
    "Upload these two files from `phase3_outputs_lof/`:\n",
    "- `encoder_simplified.onnx`\n",
    "- `encoder_int8.onnx`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "upload",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from google.colab import files\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Upload encoder_simplified.onnx and encoder_int8.onnx\")\n",
    "uploaded = files.upload()\n",
    "print(f\"\\nUploaded: {list(uploaded.keys())}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3 — Check GPU"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "check_gpu",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import subprocess\n",
    "result = subprocess.run(['nvidia-smi'], capture_output=True, text=True)\n",
    "if result.returncode == 0:\n",
    "    print(result.stdout)\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"No GPU detected — make sure runtime is set to GPU T4\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4 — Load models and inspect"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "load_models",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import onnx\n",
    "import onnxruntime as ort\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import time\n",
    "\n",
    "FP32_PATH = \"encoder_simplified.onnx\"\n",
    "INT8_PATH = \"encoder_int8.onnx\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Read input shape directly from ONNX model (no hardcoding)\n",
    "model_fp32 = onnx.load(FP32_PATH)\n",
    "input_shape = [d.dim_value if d.dim_value > 0 else 1\n",
    "               for d in model_fp32.graph.input[0].type.tensor_type.shape.dim]\n",
    "input_shape[0] = 1  # batch size = 1\n",
    "print(f\"Input shape  : {input_shape}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "output_shape = [d.dim_value if d.dim_value > 0 else 1\n",
    "                for d in model_fp32.graph.output[0].type.tensor_type.shape.dim]\n",
    "output_shape[0] = 1\n",
    "print(f\"Output shape : {output_shape}  (embedding dim = {output_shape[-1]})\")\n",
    "\n",
    "import os\n",
    "fp32_kb = os.path.getsize(FP32_PATH) / 1024\n",
    "int8_kb  = os.path.getsize(INT8_PATH) / 1024\n",
    "print(f\"\\nFP32 size : {fp32_kb:.1f} KB\")\n",
    "print(f\"INT8 size : {int8_kb:.1f} KB  ({(1 - int8_kb/fp32_kb)*100:.1f}% smaller)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Dummy input\n",
    "dummy = np.random.rand(*input_shape).astype(np.float32)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 5 — Benchmark function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "bench_fn",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def make_session(path, provider):\n",
    "    opts = ort.SessionOptions()\n",
    "    opts.graph_optimization_level = ort.GraphOptimizationLevel.ORT_ENABLE_ALL\n",
    "    return ort.InferenceSession(path, sess_options=opts, providers=[provider])\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def benchmark(session, dummy_input, n_warmup=50, n_runs=500):\n",
    "    iname = session.get_inputs()[0].name\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Warmup\n",
    "    for _ in range(n_warmup):\n",
    "        session.run(None, {iname: dummy_input})\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Timed runs\n",
    "    t0 = time.perf_counter()\n",
    "    for _ in range(n_runs):\n",
    "        session.run(None, {iname: dummy_input})\n",
    "    elapsed_ms = (time.perf_counter() - t0) / n_runs * 1000\n",
    "\n",
    "    return elapsed_ms\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Benchmark function ready.\")\n",
    "print(f\"Available providers : {ort.get_available_providers()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 6 — Run all 4 benchmarks"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "run_cpu",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── CPU benchmarks ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "print(\"Running CPU benchmarks (500 runs each)...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "sess_cpu_fp32 = make_session(FP32_PATH, \"CPUExecutionProvider\")\n",
    "sess_cpu_int8 = make_session(INT8_PATH, \"CPUExecutionProvider\")\n",
    "\n",
    "cpu_fp32_ms = benchmark(sess_cpu_fp32, dummy)\n",
    "print(f\"  CPU FP32 : {cpu_fp32_ms:.3f} ms\")\n",
    "\n",
    "cpu_int8_ms = benchmark(sess_cpu_int8, dummy)\n",
    "print(f\"  CPU INT8 : {cpu_int8_ms:.3f} ms\")\n",
    "\n",
    "cpu_speedup = cpu_fp32_ms / cpu_int8_ms\n",
    "print(f\"  CPU INT8 speedup : {cpu_speedup:.2f}x\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "run_gpu",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── GPU benchmarks ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "if \"CUDAExecutionProvider\" not in ort.get_available_providers():\n",
    "    print(\"CUDA not available — skipping GPU benchmark.\")\n",
    "    gpu_fp32_ms = None\n",
    "    gpu_int8_ms = None\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"Running GPU benchmarks (500 runs each)...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    sess_gpu_fp32 = make_session(FP32_PATH, \"CUDAExecutionProvider\")\n",
    "    sess_gpu_int8 = make_session(INT8_PATH, \"CUDAExecutionProvider\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    gpu_fp32_ms = benchmark(sess_gpu_fp32, dummy)\n",
    "    print(f\"  GPU FP32 : {gpu_fp32_ms:.3f} ms\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    gpu_int8_ms = benchmark(sess_gpu_int8, dummy)\n",
    "    print(f\"  GPU INT8 : {gpu_int8_ms:.3f} ms\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    gpu_speedup = gpu_fp32_ms / gpu_int8_ms\n",
    "    print(f\"  GPU INT8 speedup : {gpu_speedup:.2f}x\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 7 — Summary table"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "summary",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"=\" * 62)\n",
    "print(\"  Echo-Check LOF Encoder — CPU vs GPU Benchmark\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 62)\n",
    "print(f\"  Model       : Conv2D encoder  ({output_shape[-1]}-dim embedding)\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Input shape : {input_shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  FP32 size   : {fp32_kb:.1f} KB\")\n",
    "print(f\"  INT8 size   : {int8_kb:.1f} KB  ({(1-int8_kb/fp32_kb)*100:.1f}% smaller)\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(f\"  {'Config':<25} {'Latency':>10}  {'vs CPU FP32':>12}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  {'-'*50}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  {'CPU  FP32':<25} {cpu_fp32_ms:>9.3f}ms  {'(baseline)':>12}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  {'CPU  INT8':<25} {cpu_int8_ms:>9.3f}ms  {f'{cpu_fp32_ms/cpu_int8_ms:.2f}x':>12}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if gpu_fp32_ms is not None:\n",
    "    print(f\"  {'GPU  FP32':<25} {gpu_fp32_ms:>9.3f}ms  {f'{cpu_fp32_ms/gpu_fp32_ms:.2f}x':>12}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  {'GPU  INT8':<25} {gpu_int8_ms:>9.3f}ms  {f'{cpu_fp32_ms/gpu_int8_ms:.2f}x':>12}\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f\"  {'GPU  FP32':<25} {'N/A':>10}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  {'GPU  INT8':<25} {'N/A':>10}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"  {'-'*50}\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    
  }
 ]
}
